description:
Two-Face is on the loose, but this time, he's the victim. A mob boss wants Harvey Dent's files from his DA days and will stop at nothing, including kidnapping Harvey's ex-wife, to get them.

A mobster busts Two-Face loose to get the former D.A. to plan a heist, but Dent refuses. When the mobster threatens the life of Dent's estranged ex-fiancee Grace Lamont, will even that be enough to break through the rigid guidelines set by Two-Face's madness? Or is there a part of him that's still willing to risk it all to save the woman he loved?
name: Fifty Fifty

description: "Steps" part 1! In the dark and stormy night of Gotham, a killer lies in waiting. He kills his prey with a deadly crossbow and leaves a very particular calling card. Searching furiously throughout the city, the Dark Knight attempts to find the killer, but his only hope lies with an autistic child.
name: Steps: Part One of Two

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Side by side, Challengers old and new must face the most mind-boggling unknown yet--and this time the unknown may win!
name: Last Days - Part Two of Three

description: "Hell to Pay Conclusion: An Attack of Conscience." The Justice League battles the Flash Rogue's Gallery and their avatars. Meanwhile, Wally West must face up to the deal he made with Neron (involving Linda).
name: An Attack of Conscience

description: What's the connection among John Constantine, Sir Francis Bacon, a haunted cemetery and a chicken? When suburban spirits erupt with a vengeance in a South London town, Constantine must discover that link before its too late. "Widdershins" part 2.
name: Widdershins, Part 2

description: Toxic waste dumpers attack Impulse and his friends Carol Bucklen and Preston Lindsay.And Max Mercury gets kidnapped.
name: Conflict resolutions

description: In part 1 of the 3-part "Sensitive Criminals," King Mob uses psychic methods to go back in time, revealing one of the great mysteries from the start of the series, as we learn how and why he was alive in 1924. As time and space become even more distorted, other complexities unravel.
name: Poor Little Rich Girl (Sensitive Criminals Part One)

description: Meet the malevolent Mr. Finish, Tawky Tawny's replacement pookah! Uncle Dudley's life literally gets torn to pieces as he strikes a bargain with the mysterious Mr. F that could leave Fawcett City's death toll seven people higher! Also: Something's happened to the wizard Shazam -- leaving Mary and Billy both stuck in their Captain Marvel forms! Does it have anything to do with GENESIS -- coming next month?
name: The Lost Soul

description:
As our heroes head south for New Orleans, Jesse decides to take the angel's advice to heart. Plus, the triumphant return of one of PREACHER's most requested characters.

Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy head west, hoping to find the secret that's been buried in Jesse's head by Genesis; the return of Arseface!
name: Old Familiar Faces

description: Grounded and confined to his room, Tim learned of a hostage situation in town from TV. While mowing the next day, Bruce told him about how it went down. Ulysses Hadrian Armstrong, aka The General, hooked up with Arabs preparing for war with a neighboring country while they were in town at an arms show.
name: Grounded!

description: The cast of the hit radio drama "The Coming of Night" has been decimated by the grisly real-life murders of two actors. As his investigation sheds light on the twisted relationships among the show's stars and producers, the Golden Age Sandman learns there's far more drama behind the scenes than anything that happens on air.
name: The Crone, Act Two of Four

description:
Attempting to explain his recent bloodlust, the Spectre heads to Heaven, only to find it empty. Now his quest must take him downward.

Spectre searches through Heaven, Limbo and Hell but Yahweh is absent in all of them.
name: The Search for God Part One: A Measure of Pain

description:
Banding together to save the life of Solomon Grundy, Jack Knight, Batman, Sentinel and the Floronic Man enter the mind of the former villain and find a virtual army of past versions of Grundy. But as the battle rages, Grundy's physical body grows weaker, nearing death.

Jack Knight, Alan Scott, Batman and the Floronic Man take a fantastic journey inside the splintered psyche of Solomon Grundy where they meet Cyrus Gold!
name: Merry Pranksters

description: When Superman starts to exhibit signs of slowing down on the superheroics, the media begins to turn against him--even Lois Lane! As Lois hunts down the reason behind Superman's sudden change, she finds an answer that rocks her to the core!
name: The War Within

description:
In the near future, gonzo journalist/cult author Spider Jerusalem lives fast and loose in The City--a chaotic melting pot of cultures, subcultures, lifeforms, and technologies. Mastermind writer Warren Ellis (THE AUTHORITY) delivers this sharp, manic, anything-goes extrapolation of urban life.

The issue opens with a view of mountain top along with a flurry of insults towards the "whore hoppers" by our main character Spider Jerusalem.

The "Whore hoppers" are the people who have Spider on contract have become sick of him sitting up in the mountains without giving them a single book. And he has a contract that if not listened too could have dire consequences for his life. So in a manner of not so tasteful words, he agrees to come back to the city, for within the city he is the best at writing.

He gets into the city and is immediately over run by the noises and the people he left it for five years ago. He meets up with his editor at THE WORD, who gives him a deadline the first time he's back eight thousand printable words. All Spider asks for is a apartment and silence. He gets neither, well he does get an apartment but not to the standards he would have enjoyed.

Spider finds his first column...an old friend by the name of Fred Christ.
name: The Summer of the Year

description: Deathwatch! Diana lies at deaths door while all around her; events continue to unfold that will have an important impact on everyone in her life! Featuring poignant appearances by Superman, Batman, Green Lantern Kyle Rayner, Flash, and Martian Manhunter as the Worlds Greatest Super Heroes say goodbye to one of their own.
name: Deathwatch

description: Jane and the 22 Brides are on the hunt for a missing girl and a serial killer that leads her underground.
name: A Place Too Bright For Dying
The Castle Of Doctor Monstro! Part 1

description:
Anxious to have an exclusive licensing deal, Barbaric proposes to Ricochet, assuming that there would be public outcry if action figures were produced of unwed and underage parents.

An all-wedding issue!

Dragon and Alex track down the real culprit behind the decapitations - the mysterious costumed woman, Guillotine, a stripper who took out her frustrations on the clients that "touched" her. Dragon defeats Guillotine, and soon afterwards, the missing heads of the decapitated bodies are found in her apartment. Jennifer Murphy is freed from prison on account that she acted in self-defense and had no prior knowledge of her superhuman abilities. She is also awarded custody of her child, Angel, and Dragon resumes his rocky relationship with Rapture.

When Cog promises to answer Sam and Twitch's questions, they follow him into the deepest parts of Rat City. Twitch takes notes as Cog tells the tale of Spawn's confused existence as it relates to them. They view Spawn's throne and hear of his life as it was on earth before he returned as a Hellspawn. At the tour's end, Cog tells the detectives that Spawn has chosen them to help recapture his lost humanity.
name: The Past

description: By the White Queen betrayed.
name: By the White Queen Betrayed!

description: When one door closes, another one opens. Hercules takes a leave of absence to deal with his excessive drinking, while Luke Cage joins the team full-time!
name: Give & Take

description: Ka-zar is reunited with Zabu, but the reunion is short lived as Parnival Plunder sends Rhino to destroy his brother.
name: Life in the Big City
D.E.A.D. to Rights!

description: This is very reminiscent of a Star Trek original series episode when Montgomery Scott was possessed by an evil spirit.  In this comic Phillip Boyce is possessed by spirits whom want revenge and he has been possessed for a long time without even knowing it.  It this case the spirits wanted revenge and it took the Vulcan ambassador named Toluk to help.
name: Immortal Wounds

description: An away team stumbles across something that brings out their worst fears.
name: Secret Lives; As Flies To Wanton Boys

description: On a desperate rescue mission, the U.S.S. Voyager and her crew become trapped as victims themselves! If that wasn't enough, there are pirates off the starboard! With all of Voyager's systems rendered inoperable, it looks like it's time for some good old fashioned hand-to-hand combat!
name: Dead Zone

description:
Love blossoms among the Thunderbolts but will Citizen V allow it to survive?

The Thunderbolts fight the Elements of Doom.

(No relation to Doctor Doom)
name: Unstable Elements!

description: This issue also features parodies of Micronauts.
name: The Greatest Secret in the Marvel Universe Revealed!

description: From out of the fire, comes a savior... But who is it?
name: Coming Home

description: Sean Cassidy and Emma Frost decide to allow a non-mutant student into the Xavier Institute for an exclusive summer-research program!
name: Primal

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Katchoo falls.    

Falls a single floor onto a wider balcony below and lands at Darcy's feet. Darcy reveals that Rachael was in fact Veronica. 
 
Francine is frantic that Katchoo failed to ring home last night as promised. She becomes so worried she breaks out the dossier Walsh gave to Katchoo and sees the photographs for the first time and sees what kind of things Katchoo did while working for Darcy.  
  
She goes to Walsh with the suspicion that Darcy has kidnapped Katchoo or something worse. 
  
David is surprised to come down to breakfast with Darcy and Katchoo.
name: The Loneliness of Madmen

description: The story of Ruby (one of the Juris) who was killed by racists in the 1960s.
name: The Book of Law, Chapter Two of Five: Ruby/The Road To You, Being There: Part Two

description:
Kirby Hero, Kevin Matchstick, and Joe Phat have lunch and get to know each other better.  Wally Ut shows up uninvited and continues to ramble on about being Kevin's second mage, and to offer unsolicited advice.  While not altogether sane, he does seem to have at least some powers.  However, the heroes continue to ignore him and once again drive off.  They are trying to figure out what's going on.  It used to be that they could find a "nasty" in every town or so, but now there are strange groupings.  The nasties seem to be on the move, and they don't know why.  They go to the house of Isis, a witch, to see if she can offer any advice.
 
The Pale Incanter is seen building a huge golem.  He seems to have some direct connection to Kevin's power, waking up whenever it is used.
name: Two Truths Are Told

description: Daredevil, caught in a riot at Ryker’s Island! Mr. Fear has flooded the prison with his fear gas, but before Daredevil can face Fear, he must take down a new Gladiator. And this one is deadlier than the last.
name: Cruel & Unusual Punishments

description:
There's trouble in paradise. Woody's antics keep the duo from being taken seriously as superheroes. And things only get worse when Quantum and Woody try to defuse a hostage situation in a mall.

Quantum wants to be taken seriously as a hero, and he'll go to any lengths to prove it. But, how can he be taken seriously when he's stuck with Woody? How do they deal with a serious hostage situation in Manhattan Mall? How else? Badly! All this and a goat, too.
name: Noogie

description: First appearance of Zip-Kid. Details on the origin of Junior.
name: Cry Me a River of Nigh-Irresistablle Beams!
Finder

description:
In the twisted storybook land of Nevernevernarniozbia, Franklin Richards, Leech, Artie Maddicks, Tana Nile, Howard the Duck and the unexpectedly verbal Man-Thing are confronted by the Dark Hunter, who states he is for Franklin.  The good witch called Strange arrives to dispell the form of the Dark Hunter, then spirits the group to another fantasy land, this time resembling the works of Dr. Seuss. 
When they can't get the hang of speaking in verse, they are arrested and jailed by the Cadence Police.  The Dark Hunter finds them in the jail and the group breaks free, but the persuing Hunter kidnaps Artie. 
Howard appeals to the Man-Thing to try to teleport them to where they can rescue Artie, despite the fact that that power was one the muck monster exhibited only once before.  Still, he tries, and the crew find themselves on Duckworld, where Howard has been worshipped as a mega-celebrity.
name: Across the Universe
The Replacement God

description:
Tempest goes to Tritonis and frees the Poseidonians, who migrate back to the city; Tempest then finds Dolphin, and they start a relationship; Aquaman, after allowing the Poseidonians back, finds Tempest and Dolphin together.

The citizens of Poseidonis have finished rebuilding Tritonis but at the cost of breaking their proud spirits much to Vulko and Koryak's immense anger. Koryak then goes to the palace to confront Iqula on releasing the citizens from their vow of slavery Aquaman made, with Iqula challenging Koryak to a fight in accordance with the ancient ways for their fate. However Garth returns accepting the fight in his place in order to return the favor to the Atlanteans for long ago accepting him when his own people would not., Garth then makes himself a human sacrifice for Iqula's anger, but he is unable to kill him freeing the people before leaving.

While elsewhere Aquaman is enjoying his new ability to look outward with his telepathy to access The Clear. He then senses Porm who questions his continual use of force. He is then awakened from his vision of Porm and returns home with Nomek. While Tempest returns to Dolphin to let her know he has freed the citizens, while she lets him know of her growing fear of Aquaman. Tempest then prepares to leave with Dolphin desiring for him to stay longer with her,while Deep Blue oversees the citizens migration back to Poseidonis. Arthur then heads to Deep Blue's place to find Dolphin to make amends, only to catch her kissing Garth before leaving telling him he hopes he can make her happy. While back in the city Vulko tells Koryak of his vision for the future, that he will one day rule.
name: Homecoming

description: Cable's next target is Zero Tolerance leader Bastion!
name: Moving Target Part Two: Siege

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Deadpool is hired to save a young woman but things aren't as they seem. The young woman is actually Typhoid Mary in disguise. She battles with him and toys with innocent bystanders trying to get Deadpool's "inner villain" to re-appear. She fails.
name: We Don't Need Another Hero...

description: A clobbering from a Deadside-returned Jack Boniface helps Zero remember the vodou bokor responsible for making a soulless assassin of him. It's time for some payback, if he can keep from getting dead again.
name: Nothing is True, Part 3

description:
The X-Men are lost in space!

After the cockpit of their starship plummeted through a damaged stargate, Beast, Gambit, Rogue, Joseph and Trish Tilby find themselvesseparated and scattered about what appears to be an alien landscape. Gambit is captured by bounty hunters Spat and Grovel (a giant reptile), whom he had betrayed in Madagascar in the past.

In the sewers beneath Manhattan, Callisto recuperates from her wounds and encourages Marrow to aid the X-Men.

Joseph and Rogue determine their environment is illusory, and Joseph's power overwhelms the illusion created by Spat and Grovel's ally Landscape. The actual locale is a cavern somewhat familiar to Joseph.

In Pine Bluff, South Carolina, Maggott is still tracking Joseph, and has a run-in with some rednecks, who are frightened off by his truck-eating slugs.

Eventually, Spat, Grovel and Gambit cross paths with Joseph, Rogue and Landscape, then all are confronted by Magneto's Nanny robot (thought to have been destroyed in the Antarctic base of Magneto).
name: Big Night

description:
PKNA #9

Le sorgente della Luna / Springs of the Moon
name: Le sorgenti della Luna

description: Luse is on trail and decides not to wait for the verdict. Sanctuary finds out about Cassy's death in the process.
name: Sactuary Book 5: The Wolf One:  Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

name: La Tormenta part 2 of 3

description: "Drinking Buddies!" Donna Troy cameo. At long last, find out why Kyle was in that alleyway the night he received his Power Ring (see Green Lantern #50). Plus, what was the tragic news Donna Troy got at the end of last issue?
name: Drinking Buddies

deck: Supergirl is attacked in her dreams by Daemon.
description: Linda Danvers gets rid of an Incubi by luring it into a deadly dream.
name: Incubus

description: Everyone is gunning for Mitch: his wife, her boyfriend, the mob, the crooked police of Viceroy and Hooker and the Body Doubles. After another violent confrontation, Mitch comes back to life in the form of a monstrous creature that cannot be stopped!
name: Scorpion Memories, Part 3

description: A punk in Dick's neighborhood named Tad began trying to clean up the streets. Soames survived - though in a coma (his head still facing backwards). Dick helped out a street kid; Batman showed up in his apartment.
name: Mutt

description: Wedding bells are ringing for a pair of Legion love-birds, and it wouldn't be a wedding if there wasn't some problem to deal with—and this one's a doozy!
name: Til Death

description: OverviewWhen the NYPD needs help tracking a brutal serial murderer, they call on Tarzan. But even he's confused when he finds two scents where there should be one! The killer is two different people in a single body, and that spells double trouble for the Lord of the Jungle!
name: Tooth and Nail (Part 1 of 2)

description: The Revenge Squad has decided to take down the World's Greatest Super-heroes!
name: Rock of Ages, Prologue: Genesis and Revelations
Speak Now...or Forever Rest in Peace

description: John Irons is convinced something is terribly wrong with the world--and, thanks to the events of GENESIS, he's right. He's so convinced that he puts on his armor and jets over to Metropolis in search of the other Man of Steel--Superman!
name: Vertigo

description: Spurred by visions of nuclear disaster, Doctor Tomorrow races to dismantle the Nazi atomic program. But guarding it is the X-O of the 40s, the Teutonic Knight! Can Tomorrow's future tech defeat a threat from beyond our world? Can he even survive intact?
name: Black Water

description: Ninjak and Colin King's big wedding showdown continues!
The Citadel wants the X-O armor back from Donovan Wylie and they're sending in the Hard Corps to reclaim it!
name: Mind War

description: OverviewA madman with the strength of a bull ape stalks the cobblestoned alleys of Manhattan, his brain a peculiar dialogue between the power of the intellect and the nature of the beast. Tarzan must stop him before he can kill again, but not before he reflects upon his own similarity to the man/monster that is Jekyll and Hyde!
name: Tooth and Nail (Part 2 of 2)

description: The great sword Grasscutter has always been an important national treasure to the people. The recovery of the lost sword of the Gods will aid the Conspiracy of Eight in their quest to overthrow the Shogunate and reinstate the Emperor. With the help of a sorceress and the souls of dead warriors, they plan to recover the lost sword. But they didn't factor Usagi Yojimbo into their plans!
name: Grasscutter, Chapter 1: Jei

description:
Like everyone else in the world, Batman feels the despair caused by the events of GENESIS. But that doesn't stop him from saving a woman from committing suicide and enlisting Oracle in an attempt to save others who may be about to commit some final, terrible act.

Genesis tie-in.
name: Dark Genesis

description: Killer Croc has escaped, and he's fallen hard for the only person who's shown him any kindness: Summer Gleason. This spells very bad luck for Summer's football player boyfriend and Batman and Robin who are all in Croc's way!
name: Crocodile Tears

description: A killer is on the loose in Gotham City, and neither the Batman nor the police have any clues to who it is. The answer lies within an autistic child, one who seems to live in his own world. Though the Batman attempts to piece together the puzzle on his own, he fails. Now that his original suspect is also a victim, the Dark Knight has no choice but to seek help from the person he can't seem to get through to.
name: Steps: Part Two of Two

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Outmatched by Cybercat's high-tech might, the Feline Fatale acquires a high-powered new costume of her own, but even that may not be enough to defeat her persistent foe.

Tagline: "Enter a new feline fury?"
name: Cats in the Night

description: Challengers old and new battle the unknown side by side! What is the final fate of the original Challenger team, and will they take their successors with them?
name: Last Days - Part Three of Three

description: Batman and Superman in a 1920s pulp adventure; a play on the phrase "World's Finest", a long running DC Comics series feature these two heroes.

The fastest man alive meets The Suit, a new and deadly menace confronting the Flash with one of the greatest challenges of his career... a challenge that leaves him crippled, possibly never to run again.
name: Emergency Stop Part 1 of 3

description: John's friends are in danger from a crazed psyhcopath...and one of them is about to give birth!
name: Life and Death and Taxis

description: The Genisis month goes on while people all over Manchester lose hope of everything.And Impulse loses his superspeed but gets the ability to shrink and have explosive touch while saving people who have locked themselves in a vault.Max Mercury get kidnapped by an old friend,Dr. Morlo,who,at that time,wanted revenge.While Helen Claiborne stops her neighbor from committing suicide in her garage(probably the guy lost hope of life?).
name: Everything sucks

description: Shazam is missing; the Marvels get stuck in their adult forms.
name: The Gods Must Be Crazy!

description:
Jesse and his crew hit New Orleans on a hot Saturday night. Pale bloodsuckers creep from the shadows and a butt-ugly old favorite lines up his gunsights on Reverend Custer's head. And just what is that business with the photo of Cassidy all about?

Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy meet Xavier, an old friend of Cass' and a lord of Voodoo; Cassidy's history begins to catch up with him.
name: Good Times Rolling

description:
Notes:

  • Ranked #85 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: Dark at Dawn

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: As a string of murders expands its reach from actors to executives, Wesley Dodds realizes that the killer seeks the complete downfall of America's young wireless industry. Suspects abound, but it's a midnight visit to an uneasy ally that provides solid clues.
name: The Crone, Act Three of Four

description: The search for the divine brings the Spectre into conflict with deities from other pantheons. Genesis crossover.
name: The Source of All Things

description:
Infernal Devices, part 6 of 6! Respects are paid to the dead, and the cast slowly begins to disperse. But before the final curtain can be drawn, Dr. Pip has one ultimate infernal device--the madman begins his suicide assault on Opal City in an exo-suit laced with explosives!

Returning from the splintered mind of Solomon Grundy, Ted, Jack, Alan Scott and the O'dares are confronted by the infernal Mr. Pip. When the Genesis wave hits, only The Shade has the ability to face Pip.
name: Mr. Pip and Mr. Black

description: After discovering the truth behind Superman's sudden lapse in heroic duties, Lois Lane teams with Professor Hamilton to save the day. But will they get to the Man of Steel in time? And what unexpected player stands in their way?
name: The War Within, Part Two

description:
Now reacclimated to The City, Spider Jerusalem ventures into the dangerous Angels 8 district, home of the Transients--humans who have decided to become aliens through cosmetic surgery. But Spider's penetrating interview with the Transients' leader may get him a scoop he didn't bargain for.

The issue begins with Spider looking for Fred, and he walks through a town in which most of the population has "altered" their DNA to be something else called "Transients", Transients have alien appearances but some look more human or at least half.

He "asks" a transient where Fred Christ is and gets the general info from the man. As he continues his search he comes upon one of Fred's many wives, he asks her where Fred is. She (obviously terrified) tells him.

He finds Freds bar and knocks two guards out cause they were becoming irritating and lets himself into the bar. A slightly irritated Fred comes out of his room to find Spider standing there ..just waiting. They proceed to have a conversation about the transients and the town they live in, and due to Fred's lack of help in either one of the cases.. a heated debate erupts ending with Spider leaving Fred to his own pain.

Spider arrives home to meet a new friend named KAT. A two faced gecko eating cat that was sitting on his front porch. He feels "Kat" is an outcast from society, much like himself so he adopts him.

Later that night while watching Feedsites he hears that the transients have started a riot that Spider knows full well they won't win. He heads out to do another column on the riot and help them.
name: Down the Dip

description: Diana is dead…but on high Olympus, Zeus has decided that he cannot allow this soul to perish, so he grants her the greatest gift of all – transfiguration from mortal to the goddess of truth! Meanwhile, on Earth, the legend of Wonder Woman will live on when Hippolyta, changed by the events of GENESIS, takes up her daughter's mantle.
name: Where Have All The Heroes Gone?

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover
